data.title: Nature
data.meta_description:
1 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document discusses several "smallest" and "longest" superlatives related to the Philippines:

- Taal Volcano is the world's smallest volcano at 406 meters high within a lake. 

- The Philippine bamboo bat is the smallest bat species at 4 cm long with a 15 cm wingspan. 

- The Philippine mouse deer is the world's smallest hoofed mammal at 40 cm tall.

- The Philippine tarsier is the world's smallest primate at 12 cm long. 

- The dwarf goby fish, found in Malabon River, is the world's smallest vertebrate at 1.2 cm or less.

- Sy Yinchow from
